Some of the beers to be showcased at the sessions include a gin and tonic flavoured beer, in addition to the odd-sounding seafood, chocolate and wasabi flavours.

In addition to tastings, workshops will also be held for festival ticketholders.

Just like the odd brews being showcased, the classes promise not to be your average class.

Workshops include 'The Art of Spooning,' a celebration of the strange things that happen when weird brewers collaborate.

